    "question_id" : 1972392,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>The only thing I would suggest is caching the result of <code>values()</code> because each call copies an array. Also, don't create a <code>Random</code> every time. Keep one. Other than that what you're doing is fine. So:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public enum Letter {\n  A,\n  B,\n  C,\n  //...\n\n  private static final List&lt;Letter&gt; VALUES =\n    Collections.unmodifiableList(Arrays.asList(values()));\n  private static final int SIZE = VALUES.size();\n  private static final Random RANDOM = new Random();\n\n  public static Letter randomLetter()  {\n    return VALUES.get(RANDOM.nextInt(SIZE));\n  }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
