    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Combining the suggestions of <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/users/18393/cletus\">cletus</a> and <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/users/9686/helios\">helios</a>,</p>\n\n<pre><code>import java.util.Random;\n\npublic class EnumTest {\n\n    private enum Season { WINTER, SPRING, SUMMER, FALL }\n\n    private static final RandomEnum&lt;Season&gt; r =\n        new RandomEnum&lt;Season&gt;(Season.class);\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        System.out.println(r.random());\n    }\n\n    private static class RandomEnum&lt;E extends Enum&lt;E&gt;&gt; {\n\n        private static final Random RND = new Random();\n        private final E[] values;\n\n        public RandomEnum(Class&lt;E&gt; token) {\n            values = token.getEnumConstants();\n        }\n\n        public E random() {\n            return values[RND.nextInt(values.length)];\n        }\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Edit: Oops, I forgot the bounded type parameter, <code>&lt;E extends Enum&lt;E&gt;&gt;</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
